The paper discusses the technological underpinnings of the Web of Data, which involves representing, querying, and manipulating data. This aligns with the focus of the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions metadata on music, books, and scholarly articles, which falls under the digital libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. The discussion of legal and licensing issues around publicly exposed data aligns with the cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions social network representations, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
